Stats
A skilled Necromancer is both experienced and intelligent. As
such, intelligence provides the biggest contribution to maximum
spell points. The next most effective stat is constitution. A
Necromancer must have a great deal of stamina to summon ranks of
the undead, which constitution provides. Additionally,
constitution improves the minions summoned. Two other important
stats are wisdom and charisma. Wisdom strengthens a Necromancer's
bond with the otherwordly. Charisma helps Necromancers maintain
the bond over their undead minions. As stats are increased with
the Metaphysician, they provide additional power to a
Necromancer's ability to recharge their ~>runes<~. Necromancers
receive a single hit point per constitution. For energy,
a Necromancer will receive 6 SP per intelligence, 3 SP per
constitution, and 3 SP per every two wisdom or charisma
(independently of each other).

An additional, but highly influential stat, is a Necromancer's
study and perversion of the dead. This is measured by the number
of corpses desecrated. As a Necromancer desecrates more
corpses, their body can be consumed by the spirits of those
they've condemned, instantly clearing their ability cooldowns.
Higher desecration will also increase their damage capabilities,
as well as enhancing other spells.
